#Text=Over the past few months , the Modern Whig Party has been steadily increasing in membership .
#Text=Around this time last year , the MWP had under 5,000 members .
#Text=Today , that number has grown to nearly 30,000 .
#Text=In your opinion , what is the reason for the MWP 's sudden and rapid increase and popularity ?
#Text=Do you expect it to continue growing at this pace ?
#Text=As the word continues to get out about our organization , we do expect the Modern Whig Party to maintain its steady growth .
#Text=A number of print and broadcast media outlets have even gone so far as to proclaim that the Modern Whig Party is " potentially viable , " and " makes sense . "
#Text=Another outlet stated that this organization is the " fastest growing political movement in the nation . "

column1: #Text=Perhaps the main reason we continue to gain traction is that these media outlets are recognizing that the Modern Whig Party is attractive to moderate Democrats , independents and disenchanted Republicans .
#Text=At the same time , we are building this organization realistically , methodically and gradually in an effort to get this right .
#Text=How exactly does the Modern Whig Party differ from America 's two largest political parties ; the Republican and Democratic ?

#Text=One important difference between the Modern Whig Party and the other two parties is that we look beyond partisan rivalry and will absolutely support a candidate or elected official from a different party if that person subscribes to a doctrine of common sense and rational solutions rather than ideology .
#Text=We realize that most people are not limited to one distinct ideology and instead pick and choose based on specific issues .
#Text=Is your party running any candidates for federal or statewide office in the 2010 midterm elections ?
#Text=Our strategy is to refrain from trotting out as many candidates as possible just to lose .
#Text=Instead , we are diverting our resources and focus to a relatively small group of initial candidates who bring quality and viability to the table .
#Text=We are continuing the vetting process for our potential candidates .
#Text=So far , we have two announced candidates running for office .
#Text=A well-qualified candidate named Gene Baldassari is running for the New Jersey State Assembly in the 14th District .
#Text=That election is November 2009 .
#Text=In addition , Paul McKain is running for Congress in Florida 's 2nd Congressional District .
#Text=Paul McKain is a prominent entrepreneur , retired firefighter and recognized child-safety advocate who brings a wealth of down-to-earth experience and qualifications .
#Text=Currently , are there any elected officials in the United States that are members of the Modern Whig Party ?
#Text=We have some prominent members who have signed onto this organization to include military generals , former GOP county/state officials and current/former elected officials on the local level .
#Text=However , we do not have any elected officials on the Whig ticket as we still are a newly constituted political organization .
#Text=In fact , many of our members remain on the GOP and Democratic rolls , which again , is something that we have no problems with as we continue to build .
